# LLM Provider Configuration for practice_031c_agentic_production_patterns
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values for your chosen provider.
# All variables are optional — defaults work with a local Ollama container.
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # Edit .env with your settings, then:
#   export $(cat .env | xargs) && uv run python src/02_guardrails.py

# Provider selection. Options: ollama (default), lmstudio, openai, anthropic, google
# LLM_PROVIDER=ollama

# Model name. Defaults per provider:
#   ollama/lmstudio → qwen2.5:7b
#   openai          → gpt-4o-mini
#   anthropic       → claude-3-haiku-20240307
#   google          → gemini-1.5-flash
# LLM_MODEL=qwen2.5:7b

# Base URL override. Defaults:
#   ollama   → http://localhost:11434
#   lmstudio → http://localhost:1234/v1
#   cloud providers use their SDK defaults (leave unset)
# LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434

# API key. Required for cloud providers (openai, anthropic, google).
# Ignored for local providers (ollama, lmstudio).
# LLM_API_KEY=sk-...
